Fred T. HANSEN v. UNITED STATES of America.* No. 5900. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 7, 1936. Thomas B. Hart, of Chicago, 111., for appellee.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges, and LINDLEY, District Judge.

Writ of certiorari denied 57 S.Ct. 491, 81 L.Ed. —r-.

 PER CURIAM.

Now this day come the parties by their counsel and this cause now comes on to be heard on the printed record and briefs of counsel and on oral arguments.

On consideration whereof it is now here ordered and adjudged by this court that the judgment of the District Court of the United States for the Northern District of Illinois, Eastern Division, in this cause be, and the same .is hereby, affirmed.
